You are working in a professional backend project using:

- Node.js
- NestJS with Fastify adapter
- TypeORM
- PostgreSQL
- Modular architecture

Before generating any code, always read and follow:

- docs/architecture.md
- docs/api-guidelines.md
- docs/security-guidelines.md
- docs/nest-conventions.md
- docs/testing-guidelines.md
- docs/coding-standards.md

Rules:

- Follow RESTful principles strictly.
- Use NestJS built-in exceptions.
- Controllers must be thin.
- Use cases must contain business logic.
- Always use dependency injection.
- Use JWT with HttpOnly cookies.
- Write tests for all use cases.
- Use TypeORM repositories via @InjectRepository.
- Import DatabaseModule in modules that need database access.

Never:

- Put business logic inside controllers.
- Access database directly outside repositories.
- Break NestJS module boundaries.

Formatting Enforcement:

- Always respect project Prettier configuration.
- Respect max line width.
- Break long type definitions into multiline.
- Always include trailing commas where required.
- Generate formatted code as if Prettier --write was executed.
